He was speaking at the main Human Rights Day in Sharpeville, outside Johannesburg, on Wednesday. 

The event marked the 58th commemoration of the 1960 Sharpeville Massacre where 69 people were killed by the apartheid government during an anti-Pass march organised by the Pan African Congress (PAC). 

Thousands turned out for the commemoration event including several cabinet ministers, the commissioner of the Human Rights Commission and PAC President, Narius Moloto. Ntebo Mokobo was there.... --SABC--